The Dehli School of Economics is a prestigious academic institution in India. It was formed in 1949 when a group of visionaries led by Professor V.K.R.V. Rao and supported by India's first Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru launched a project to create a centre for advanced studies in the social sciences. The school has a department of economics, sociology and geography. This school has several well known and world renowned individuals in its list of present and former faculty, like Amartya Sen and the current Prime Minister of India, Manmohan Singh. Several Alumni from the economics department of this school have been very successful worldwide.

column10: The Gujrat Riots were the result of the burning of the Sabarmati Express train at Godhra city in the state of Gujarat. This took place on February 27, 2002 when the train was forcibly attacked by a large Muslim mob. This resulted in the death of many Hindu passengers who were returning from the holy city of Ayodhya and consequently severe massacres and riots that led to the death of many thousand Hindus and Muslims.

column10: Zamindars were officials employed by the Mughals to collect taxes from the peasants. This system was then used by the British as well but was abolished after independence.
